00:02:15.969 --> 00:02:18.013
Lets check out UFocus™.

00:02:18.013 --> 00:02:21.308
This feature lets you snap a picture and refocus after the shot 

00:02:21.308 --> 00:02:22.684
has been taken.

00:02:22.684 --> 00:02:25.646
Just tap on the area of the photo you would like to be in focus and

00:02:25.646 --> 00:02:27.189
the rest is blurred.

00:02:27.189 --> 00:02:30.400
Now, you can change the center of attention in any photo, and create

00:02:30.400 --> 00:02:33.737
a beautiful Bokeh effect.

00:02:33.737 --> 00:02:37.741
With Dimension Plus™, add 3D-like depth and dimension to an image.

00:02:37.741 --> 00:02:40.827
Once your image is captured, tap the Edit icon,

00:02:40.827 --> 00:02:43.455
choose Dimension Plus from the effects menu.

00:02:43.455 --> 00:02:46.333
Tilt the phone up and down and see how the image becomes three

00:02:46.333 --> 00:02:48.502
dimensional before your eyes.

00:02:48.502 --> 00:02:53.048
Or to create a 360-degree panoramic -- choose Pan 360.

00:02:53.048 --> 00:02:56.259
Simply focus on your frame view and match the box with the center

00:02:56.259 --> 00:02:58.178
brackets until it becomes red.

00:02:58.178 --> 00:03:00.722
Continue to match the box with the brackets all the way around the

00:03:00.722 --> 00:03:02.724
picture you would like to create.

00:03:02.724 --> 00:03:06.687
Pan 360 will compile all the pictures into one full, high definition

00:03:06.687 --> 00:03:10.065
360 degree shot of your surroundings!

